Well, Doc Spatz, you have just been obliterated by the most profound six tube SP 8&quot; 50m height of burst (HOB) firecracker (FC) time on target (TOT) registration I have seen anywhere on this site. We even have a little 4.2 illumination to be sure that everyone sees it! Thousands of tiny butterfly bombs are gently falling, hitting the ground, bouncing back up 2 or 3m, exploding, and obliterating everything with a three dimensional cloud of frag grenade wire shards traveling in all directions at greater than the speed of sound.<br><br>
That's real bad.<br><br>
The bunnies have pulled high explosive (HE) rounds and time delay (TD) fuses for the next event. They are planning a high angle bunker and tunnel busting party. It is not as pretty as FC TOT's, but it is nasty. 8&quot; HE TD burrows in real deep under the ground in tropical alluvial soil, and then detonates. High angle makes it worse because of the max ord and high terminal velocity upon round impact. This is really rough white bag stuff. The azimuth, range, and elevation have already been laid in.<br><br>
...and all you have been doing is sitting under a straw hat.<br><br>
My advice?<br><br>
Hide.
